We definitely need a proper solution baked into `TextField` and `TextFormField`. But in the meanwhile, the [auto_size_text_field](https://pub.dev/packages/auto_size_text_field) package might help you out a little bit:

```dart
AutoSizeTextField(
  controller: _controller,
  overflowReplacement: Text(
  _controller.text,
  style: const TextStyle(overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis),
),
```


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43783196/138687452-81541ee5-4ca1-4d35-9ff2-12fb2554665e.mov



But be aware it's not a perfect solution. Try out the full example and you'll see why:

<details>
<summary>Full example</summary>
<br>

```dart
import 'package:auto_size_text_field/auto_size_text_field.dart';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() => runApp(const MyApp());

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const MaterialApp(
      home: HomePage(),
    );
  }
}

class HomePage extends StatefulWidget {
  const HomePage();

  @override
  State<HomePage> createState() => _HomePageState();
}

class _HomePageState extends State<HomePage> {
  static const _style = TextStyle(color: Colors.black, fontSize: 15, overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis);
  final _controller = TextEditingController();

  @override
  void dispose() {
    _controller.dispose();
    super.dispose();
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          decoration: BoxDecoration(
            border: Border.all(),
            borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(5),
          ),
          width: 200,
          child: Padding(
            padding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 8),
            child: AutoSizeTextField(
              controller: _controller,
              cursorColor: Colors.black,
              decoration: const InputDecoration(border: InputBorder.none),
              minFontSize: _style.fontSize!,
              onChanged: (_) => setState(() {}),
              overflowReplacement: Padding(
                padding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(vertical: 15),
                child: Text(
                  _controller.text,
                  style: _style,
                ),
              ),
              style: _style,
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
</details>

@polina-c I think this issue is not related to the devtools bug that you mentioned.

I believe this issue is about wanting something like [TextOverflow](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/painting/TextOverflow.html) for EditableText. So the video in the comment https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/61069#issuecomment-950826914 shows what I would expect a solution to this problem to do.

CC @LongCatIsLooong who's working on the overflow ellipsis right now.

