> and if so, what does the Material spec say about this?

The Material Spec does not clearly state how the caret should behave (only the cursor color is clearly specified).
The [label text section](https://m3.material.io/components/text-fields/guidelines#d65e62c9-97a4-437c-a099-23acea26e68a) specifies that label text and input text should be aligned, so moving the input text to the right will break this rule.

In the Figma Kit, the cursor is moved to the left:
![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c380f65a-baaa-48a0-a932-d733097ae4c3)

In Flutter, the cursor appears also slighly on the left of the text but this is related to font letter spacing (one empty pixel before and after each character) :

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a5ef4789-06ad-4d6b-acbf-e5b62d2ef29b)
 
The default value for `TextField.cursorWidth` is 2.0 which makes this problem more visible, with 1.0 the cursor does not overlap the text:

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a33290dc-2b5d-4bfd-9d76-eb989b2aa70e)

The Material specification does not define the default cursor width, in most of the screenshots and in the Figma Kit it seems to be 1.0 pixel. But on native Android (and Flutter) the cursor width is 2.0.


I checked the Compose demo, the rendering is similar to Flutter except that the cursor is painted underneath the hint text which is what was proposed in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/39466#issuecomment-636875938:

![Screenshot_20250108-102058](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c4521241-2c6f-493b-a03d-ee77b50a46f8)


In conlusion, the issue is exactly what was described in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/39466#issuecomment-636875938: "the proposal should be to make sure the hint text is drawn over the cursor rather than under it".

